## Claude Code Specifics

- `$TMPDIR` differs between sandbox and non-sandbox modes (sandbox: an isolated path under `/tmp/`; non-sandbox: normal user TMPDIR). A path written in one mode may not be valid in the other — re-resolve `$TMPDIR` per tool call rather than passing paths between them. `/tmp` itself isn't writable in sandbox mode; use `$TMPDIR`.
